e%20roasting%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20125%20miles%20east%20of%20Cooperative's%20roastery%20in%20Asheville%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20you'll%20find%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.summitcoffee.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESummit%20Coffee%3C%2Fa%3E's%20flagship%20location%20in%20Davidson%2C%20where%20the%20price%20of%20coffee%20increased%20by%20%240.10%20a%20cup%20in%20February.%20That's%20a%20relatively%20small%20adjustment%2C%20said%20Summit%20Coffee%20CEO%20Brian%20Helrich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Spencer%20Ford%20knows%20of%20many%20coffee%20shops%20that%20have%20had%20to%20increase%20prices%20by%20more%20than%20a%20dime%20a%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cooperative%20coffee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f908fca50259add4cd948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECooperative%20Coffee%20Roasters%20raised%20prices%20at%20its%20coffee%20shop%20in%20February%202025.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Cooperative%20Coffee%20Roasters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20is%20a%20trader%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froyalcoffee.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoyal%20Coffee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20buys%20green%20coffee%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20imports%20it%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20sells%20it%20to%20coffee%20roasters.%20Most%20of%20his%20clients%2C%20recently%2C%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20freaking%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20good%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20career%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20volatile%20time%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20just%20the%20commodity%20price%20of%20coffee%2C%20that%20we've%20ever%20seen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20When%20Ford%20first%20started%20trading%20coffee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftradingeconomics.com%2Fcommodity%2Fcoffee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20commodity%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20less%20than%20%241%20per%20pound.%20The%20previous%20commodity%20market%20high%20hit%20a%20little%20over%20%243%20back%20in%201977.%20In%20the%20fall%20of%202024%2C%20it%20started%20to%20spiral%20upward%20and%20traded%20up%20to%20%244.40%20a%20pound%20in%20the%20new%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20was%20before%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariffs%20entered%20the%20picture%20and%20further%20rattled%20the%20coffee%20industry.%20Due%20to%20a%20trifecta%20of%20climate%20factors%2C%20geopolitical%20turmoil%2C%20and%20tariff%20uncertainty%2C%20coffee%20producers%20are%20paying%20more%20and%20passing%20on%20these%20costs%20to%20consumers.%20The%20average%20price%20per%20pound%20of%20ground%20coffee%20sold%20to%20consumers%20was%20about%20%247.54%20in%20April%2C%20a%20record%20high%20and%20up%20from%20%246.06%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FAPU0000717311%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2221c2e0c4-8036-47ea-a277-80446dc97faa%5C%22%3EThe%20climate%20crisis%20and%20global%20unrest%3A%20A%20volatile%20market%20pre-tariffs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Helfrich%20started%20buying%20coffee%20in%202014%2C%20the%20coffee%20market%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20stable%20and%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20minor%20fluctuations%2C%20up%20and%20down%2020%20cents%2C%2030%20cents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spike%20to%20above%20%244%20in%20early%202025%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20a%20confluence%20of%20factors.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20that%20could%20be%20a%20variable%20has%20become%20a%20variable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Helfrich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20there's%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelfrich%20points%20to%20Brazil%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20coffee%20exporter%2C%20which%20has%20dealt%20with%20frost%20and%20severe%20drought%20in%20recent%20years.%20Extreme%20weather%20can%20hurt%20coffee%20plants%20and%20result%20in%20a%20smaller%20crop%20yield.%20If%20Brazil%20expects%20to%20produce%2030%20million%20tons%20of%20coffee%20but%2C%20in%20actuality%2C%20produces%2027%20million%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20of%20a%20sudden%20supply%20demand%20happens%20and%20people%20start%20freaking%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20that%20previous%20commodity%20market%20high%20of%20about%20%243%20in%201977%3F%20That%20was%20due%20to%20the%20so-called%20Brazilian%20black%20frost%2C%20where%20freezing%20temperatures%20kill%20plants%20without%20forming%20any%20visible%20white%20frost.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20frost%20in%20Brazil%20like%20two%20out%20of%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Ford%20said%20of%20the%20once-rare%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20general%20global%20unrest.%20Attacks%20on%20commercial%20vessels%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%2C%20for%20example%2C%20have%20disrupted%20key%20shipping%20routes.%20Helfrich%20said%20he%20had%20to%20send%20some%20of%20his%20coffee%20shipments%20on%20a%20more%20southern%20route%20to%20avoid%20attacks%2C%20which%20led%20to%20additional%20shipping%20time%20and%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225065%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cooperative%20coffee%20roasters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680fcf2c3fe8d3928364455b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223377%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFounded%20in%202019%2C%20Cooperative%20Coffee%20Roasters%20survived%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Hurricane%20Helene.%20Now%2C%20it's%20managing%20tariffs.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Cooperative%20Coffee%20Roasters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20supply%20has%20been%20decreasing%2C%20demand%20has%20been%20increasing%2C%20added%20Helfrich%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20coffee%20drinkers%20in%20the%20developing%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commodity%20price%20of%20coffee%20has%20dipped%20since%20its%20peak%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftradingeconomics.com%2Fcommodity%2Fcoffee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit's%20around%20%243.70%20per%20pound%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20of%20May%202025%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20still%20higher%20than%20it's%20ever%20been%2C%20and%20Helfrich%20expects%20it%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20%243.70s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eceb3bcc-2a8d-4191-b6c9-65ebaef23334%5C%22%3ETariffs%20add%20to%20uncertainty%20in%202025%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20have%20added%20another%20layer%20of%20complexity%20to%20the%20already%20volatile%20coffee%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooperative%20and%20Summit%20haven't%20felt%20the%20side%20effects%20of%20tariffs%20yet%2C%20since%20they%20purchase%20their%20raw%20green%20coffee%20beans%20so%20far%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20interesting%20thing.%20Coffee%20that%20was%20already%20on%20the%20water%20was%20not%20subject%20to%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McDaniel.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20it'll%20definitely%20be%20a%20downstream%20effect.%20It's%20something%20that%20we'll%20start%20seeing%20in%20coffee%20that%20arrives%20in%20June%20and%20July.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelfrich%20has%20a%20coffee%20supply%20that%20will%20last%20through%20about%20November%20and%20said%20he%20isn't%20putting%20anything%20new%20under%20contract%20right%20now%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20usual%20six-to-12-month%20runway%20we%20have%2C%20we're%20letting%20that%20get%20shorter%20and%20shorter%20and%20shorter%20in%20hopes%20that%20maybe%20that%20coffee%20market%20goes%20down%2C%20maybe%20the%20tariffs%20go%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20risk%20in%20sitting%20and%20waiting%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt'll%20come%20time%20for%20us%20to%20decide%20if%20we%20want%20our%20partner%20in%20Peru%20to%20send%20us%20a%20shipping%20container%20of%20coffee%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20locked%20it%20in%20right%20now%2C%20we'd%20be%20paying%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20fee.%20If%20we%20decide%20to%20wait%20a%20little%20bit%20and%20be%20patient%2C%20they%20might%20sell%20their%20coffee%20to%20somebody%20else%2C%20and%20then%2C%20while%20we%20might%20be%20able%20to%20get%20coffee%20at%20a%20lower%20price%2C%20the%20coffees%20we've%20always%20relied%20on%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223742%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22royal%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f9319ca50259add4cd9a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225613%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Royal%20Coffee%20warehouse%20in%20Oakland%2C%20California.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Royal%20Coffee%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHelfrich%20hasn't%20completely%20avoided%20tariffs.%20At%20the%20peak%2C%20when%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20imports%20hit%20145%25%2C%20he%20owed%20an%20extra%20four-figure%20bill%20on%20his%20coffee%20bags%2C%20which%20are%20manufactured%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20already%20paid%20our%2050%25%20deposit%20on%20the%20bags%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20produced%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20order%20to%20receive%20the%20shipment%2C%20we%20had%20to%20pay%20an%20over%20%248%2C000%20instant%20tax%20bill.%20We%20couldn't%20switch%20to%20a%20US%20producer%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20enough%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Helfrich.%20%26quot%3BIt%20more%20than%20doubled%20the%20price%20of%20our%20bags%2C%20which%2C%20across%2020-something%20thousand%20bags%2C%20hurts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord's%20company%20is%20just%20now%20starting%20to%20pay%20the%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20imported%20goods.%20Time%20will%20tell%20how%20that%20extra%20cost%20impacts%20the%20business%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20we%20can%20still%20average%20some%20of%20the%20untariffed%20stuff%20that%20we%20have%20already%2C%20so%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20raise%20everything%20so%20dramatically%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20eventually%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20run%20out%20of%20untariffed%20inventory.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227763805d-a196-4c76-9c9b-e6a43f9c015b%5C%22%3EThe%20future%20of%20coffee%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EChances%20are%2C%20your%20cup%20of%20coffee%20or%20bag%20of%20beans%20will%20start%20to%20cost%20even%20more%2C%20potentially%20as%20early%20as%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEspecially%20if%20tariffs%20persist%2C%20roasteries%20and%20caf%C3%A9s%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20have%20a%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Helfrich.%20They%20rely%20on%20importing%20because%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20cannot%20grow%20coffee.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%2C%20everybody's%20going%20to%20raise%20prices%20a%20little%20bit%20since%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20going%20back%20down.%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20get%20used%20to%20a%20slightly%20new%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cooperative%20coffee%20roasters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f93666ffb6822ec614b81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECooperative%20purchases%20coffee%20from%20smallholding%20producers%20worldwide%2C%20including%20in%20Mexico%2C%20Peru%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20Ethiopia.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Cooperative%20Coffee%20Roasters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20start%20complaining%2C%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20coffee%20might%20cost%20closer%20to%20what%20it%20always%20should%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCoffee%20has%20historically%20been%20undervalued.%20We%20take%20it%20for%20granted%20in%20the%20US%20as%20this%20cheap%20pick-me-up%2C%20and%20that%20neglects%20the%20reality%20of%20coffee%20and%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20even%20have%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McDaniel.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20agricultural%20product%20that's%20only%20grown%20in%20the%20tropics%2C%20and%20high-quality%20coffee%20is%20only%20grown%20in%20really%20high%20elevations.%20There%20is%20so%20much%20human%20labor%20associated%20with%20growing%20coffee%2C%20harvesting%20coffee%2C%20processing%20it%2C%20preparing%20it%20to%20be%20exported%2C%20and%20then%20bringing%20it%20into%20the%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20big%20a%20price%20jump%20will%20vary%20from%20business%20to%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20coffee%20companies%20that%20don't%20roast%20their%20own%20coffee%20that%20are%20going%20to%20get%20hurt%20the%20hardest%20%E2%80%94%20because%20roasters%20have%20to%20increase%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Helfrich.%20Caf%C3%A9s%20like%20his%20that%20roast%20in-house%20have%20more%20control.%20For%20the%20shops%20that%20outsource%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20roaster%20needs%20to%20raise%20its%20prices%2C%20then%20the%20coffee%20shop%20just%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20that%20accordingly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20is%20how%20much%20a%20business%20first%20raised%20its%20prices%20pre-tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDepending%20on%20whether%20the%20roastery%20or%20the%20business%20raised%20their%20prices%20enough%20initially%20to%20cover%20the%20tariff%20increase%20as%20well%2C%20then%20maybe%20they%20won't%20have%20to%20raise%20them%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ford.%20%26quot%3BBut%20my%20thinking%20is%20that%2C%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20as%20roasters%20and%20importers%20start%20running%20out%20of%20untariffed%20inventory%2C%20the%20price%20will%20go%20up%20again%20because%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20buying%20everything%20at%20the%20new%2C%20higher%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20less%20sure%20about%20how%20consumers%20will%20react.%20So%20far%2C%20he%20hasn't%20seen%20any%20drop-off%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20might%20be%20upset%2C%20but%20it%20might%20not%20stop%20them%20from%20buying%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ford.%20%26quot%3BCoffee%20consumption%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20pretty%20resilient%20to%20price%20rises.%20Now%2C%20how%20much%20they%20go%20up%20before%20people%20start%20saying%2C%20'this%20is%20crazy%2C'%20I%20don't%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-coffee-is-more-expensive-roasters-cafe-owners-prices-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748166902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f9001ca50259add4cd930%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-coffee-is-more-expensive-roasters-cafe-owners-prices-tariffs-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chances%20are%2C%20your%20cup%20of%20coffee%20or%20bag%20of%20beans%20will%20start%20to%20cost%20even%20more%20in%20a%20few%20months%2C%20as%20caf%C3%A9s%20start%20to%20feel%20the%20full%20effects%20of%20tariffs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-coffee-is-more-expensive-roasters-cafe-owners-prices-tariffs-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LinkedIn%20co-founder%3A%20Startup%20founders%20talking%20about%20work-life%20balance%20are%20not%20%E2%80%A6%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748166868000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-121390608%2Cimgsize-17734.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Flinkedin-co-founder-startup-founders-talking-about-work-life-balance-are-not-%2Farticleshow%2F121390619.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reid%20Hoffman%2C%20LinkedIn's%20co-founder%2C%20has%20sparked%20controversy%20by%20asserting%20that%20startup%20founders%20prioritizing%20work-life%20balance%20lack%20the%20dedication%20needed%20for%20su