w.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-early-with-enough-money-for-one-year-no-regrets-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748164172000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682fbb2fca50259add4cdb7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-early-with-enough-money-for-one-year-no-regrets-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Walter%20Green%20retired%20from%20his%2030-year%20IT%20career%20at%2052%20years%20old%20with%20enough%20funds%20to%20last%20him%20and%20his%20family%20one%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmartinelli%40businessinsider.com%20(Tess%20Martinelli)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A51%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-early-with-enough-money-for-one-year-no-regrets-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20worked%20as%20an%20undercover%20FBI%20agent%20for%2023%20years.%20Here's%20what%20it%20was%20like%20infiltrating%20bike%20gangs%2C%20cartels%2C%20and%20neo-Nazi%20groups.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22674%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Scott%20Payne%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6830bd1dca50259add4cf108%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22506%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScott%20Payne%20was%20an%20undercover%20agent%20for%20the%20FBI.%3Cp%3EScott%20Payne%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EScott%20Payne%20was%20an%20undercover%20agent%20and%20coordinator%20for%20the%20FBI%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPayne%20went%20undercover%20in%20motorcycle%20gangs%20and%20extremist%20groups%20to%20facilitate%20arrests.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20working%20undercover%20meant%20developing%20relationships%20that%20he%20might%20have%20to%20betray.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Scott%20Payne%2C%20a%20former%20undercover%20FBI%20agent.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20employment%20and%20certifications%20with%20documents.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20quality.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20served%20in%20the%20FBI%20for%2023%20years%2C%20mostly%20as%20an%20undercover%20agent%20infiltrating%20bike%20gangs%2C%20cartels%20and%20America's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-neo-nazism-actually-works-former-white-supremacist-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eneo-Nazi%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndercover%20work%20is%20defined%20by%20forming%20relationships%20that%20you%20may%20betray%20in%20the%20future%20and%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20how%20to%20do%20that%20without%20it%20having%20an%20adverse%20effect%20on%20your%20psyche.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20always%20fascinated%20by%20undercover%20movies%2C%20and%20I'm%20a%20people%20person.%20I%20think%20that's%20what%20drew%20me%20to%20undercover%20work.%20I%20started%20working%20as%20a%20cop%20in%201993%20and%20spent%20three%20years%20as%20a%20uniform%20patrol%20officer%2C%20then%20two%20years%20in%20vice%20and%20narcotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201998%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20work%20for%20the%20FBI%20and%20was%20accepted.%20New%20York%20City%20was%20my%20first%20office%20in%20the%20FBI%20after%20the%20academy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227f8a833-0c3e-4b0b-8fcc-1fdbd608115d%5C%22%3EFBI%20agents%20are%20investigators%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20you're%20required%20to%20be%20in%20the%20FBI%20is%20a%20case%20agent.%20You%20can%20be%20a%20firearms%20instructor%2C%20undercover%20coordinator%2C%20or%20source%20handler%2C%20but%20you're%20an%20investigator%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20undercover%20officer%20is%20voluntary.%20Every%20FBI%20field%20office%20has%20an%20undercover%20coordinator%20who%20coaches%20agents%20who%20want%20to%20get%20into%20the%20undercover%20program.%20They'll%20ask%20you%20questions%20about%20your%20life%20and%20family.%20You%20have%20to%20have%20the%20mentality%20that%20you%20can%20protect%20yourself%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you're%20waiting%20for%20the%20SWAT%20team%20to%20come%20in%2C%20it's%20not%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20selection%20process%2C%20we%20had%20psychological%20tests%20with%20a%20clinical%20psychologist.%20They%20might%20run%20you%20through%20scenarios%20and%20analyze%20your%20reactions.%20Then%2C%20the%20agents%20considering%20who%20gets%20into%20the%20program%20will%20select%2040%20candidates%20to%20get%20certified.%20It's%20a%2020-slot%20school%2C%20but%20they%20have%2020%20backups%20if%20people%20drop%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20course%20is%20two%20weeks%20of%20nonstop%20training.%20The%20undercover%20trainers%20try%20to%20expose%20your%20weaknesses.%20Are%20you%20going%20to%20drink%20while%20you're%20undercover%3F%20Do%20you%20lose%20it%20and%20start%20wanting%20to%20fight%20everyone%3F%20They're%20looking%20for%20red%20flags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20my%20undercover%20certification%20in%202002.%20Since%20I've%20been%20on%20the%20team%2C%20I've%20never%20seen%20a%20100%25%20graduation%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245decd58-607b-4876-90a4-1d9b765fd823%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20rules%20for%20undercover%20agents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can't%20be%20involved%20in%20acts%20of%20violence%20unless%20it's%20self-defense.%20We%20can't%20come%20up%20with%20a%20criminal%20idea%20because%20that%20would%20be%20an%20entrapment%20issue.%20You%20should%20never%20have%20anything%20on%20you%20that%20has%20personal%20ties%20to%20you%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndercover%20agents%20should%20never%20use%20drugs.%20If%20you're%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20you've%20taken%20drugs%2C%20you%20have%20to%20tell%20the%20case%20team%20and%20the%20United%20States%20Attorney's%20Office%20and%20get%20to%20an%20emergency%20room%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20don't%20overdose%2C%20especially%20with%20fentanyl%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228258016a-6bcd-45e8-a26e-7aaeee3933ae%5C%22%3EAs%20an%20undercover%20agent%2C%20you%20have%20to%20have%20your%20'legend%2C'%20as%20we%20call%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20legend%20is%20your%20backstory.%20When%20I%20was%20going%20deep%20undercover%2C%20I%20needed%20my%20backstory%20to%20be%20solid%20and%20believable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20usually%20used%20names%20I%20had%20associations%20with%20and%20stuck%20closely%20to%20who%20I%20was%20while%20undercover.%20I%20ride%20motorcycles%20and%20lift%20weights%2C%20and%20my%20jokes%20were%20going%20to%20be%20the%20same.%20Some%20people%20think%20it's%20dangerous%20to%20stick%20close%20to%20the%20truth%2C%20but%20I%20generally%20felt%20more%20comfortable%20using%20that%20tactic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20liked%20to%20have%20more%20than%20one%20recorder%20on%20my%20person%20in%20case%20something%20went%20wrong.%20The%20undercover%20technique%20is%20extremely%20effective%20at%20securing%20evidence.%20If%20you're%20on%20trial%20and%20the%20evidence%20you%20recorded%20cuts%20out%2C%20not%20having%20the%20full%20picture%20could%20create%20doubt%20in%20a%20jury's%20mind.%20I've%20never%20had%20to%20testify%20in%20an%20FBI%20undercover%20case%20because%20the%20evidence%20was%20always%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211d0bf0f-a96b-4d7d-86bb-4a5f2a3cbb2d%5C%22%3EI%20worked%20undercover%20in%20biker%20gangs%20and%20far-right%20groups%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20personal%20life%20and%20work%20overlapped.%20I%20shared%20a%20lot%20with%20my%20wife.%20Working%20undercover%20isn't%20like%20being%20in%20the%20military.%20I%20wouldn't%20disappear%20for%20months%20at%20a%20time.%20I%20would%20usually%20be%20gone%20for%20two-week%20stints.%20One%20thing%20I%20would%20do%20is%20take%20my%20cross%20off%20my%20necklace%20and%20put%20a%20skull%20on%20it.%20When%20I%20got%20home%2C%20I'd%20switch%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20staffed%20on%20an%20undercover%20case%2C%20FBI%20headquarters%20will%20email%20every%20undercover%20coordinator%20with%20a%20synopsis%20of%20what%20they%20need%2C%20which%20is%20circulated%20to%20the%20certified%20undercovers.%20Then%2C%20you%20can%20volunteer%20for%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20for%20some%20undercover%20work%20in%20San%20Antonio%20and%20applied.%20I%20got%20approved%20for%2030%20days%2C%20then%20became%20the%20primary.%20They%20ended%20up%20transferring%20me%20to%20the%20case%2C%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20the%20Mexican%20border.%20I%20was%20there%20as%20a%20case%20agent%2C%20working%20on%20cartel%20stuff.%20This%20was%20the%20only%20classified%20case%20I%20worked%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20infiltrated%20the%20Outlaws%20motorcycle%20gang%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20going%20undercover%20for%20three%20years%20in%202005.%20I%20earned%20their%20trust%20and%20eventually%20got%20enough%20evidence%20to%20arrest%20them%20for%20drug%20trafficking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20working%20for%20the%20Outlaws%2C%20I%20got%20very%20close%20to%20one%20of%20the%20guys%20in%20the%20gang.%20I%20remember%20rocking%20his%20newborn%20daughter%20at%20his%20house%20and%20working%20out%20together.%20When%20the%20case%20was%20over%2C%20he%20called%20me%20to%20tell%20me%20some%20of%20the%20Outlaws%20had%20been%20arrested.%20His%20last%20words%20to%20me%20were%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20said%20it%20back.%20I%20hung%20up%20probably%20as%20the%20SWAT%20team%20was%20hitting%20his%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20a%20case%20undercover%20in%20a%20white%20supremacy%20group%20called%20The%20Base.%20It%20was%20a%20group%20of%20young%20guys%20who%20wanted%20to%20accelerate%20the%20collapse%20of%20society.%20We%20found%20out%20about%20them%20through%20a%20tip%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20in%20cold%20and%20went%20to%20the%20group's%20firearms%20training%20and%20group%20meetings%20and%20became%20close%20with%20th